Getting the Power
Using the **
In [10]:
print(2**3)
print(5**2)
print(3**4)
8
25
81
Using the pow() function
In [11]:
print(pow(2,3))
print(pow(5,2))
print(pow(3,4))
8
25
81
Getting the root of a number
In [12]:
print(2**0.5)
print(3**0.5)
print(36**0.5)

print(pow(2,0.5))
print(pow(3,0.5))
print(pow(36,0.5))
1.4142135623730951
1.7320508075688772
6.0
1.4142135623730951
1.7320508075688772
6.0
Getting the remainder when a power is divided by a number.
In [13]:
print(pow(2,5,6))
print(pow(2,3,7))
2
1
Dealing with strings (String is a group of characters)
Printing the string
In [14]:
print('dog')
print("cat")
print('''giraffe''')
print("""cow""")
print('255145151515415152')
print("5154151")
